        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:21PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Bryson City, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alarka, Luada, Cowee, Almond, and Bryson City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
